    <text>
        <body>
            <head>22. Telegram From the Department of State to Secretary of State <persName
                    corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">Vance</persName> in <placeName
                    corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW">Egypt</placeName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d22fn1">Source: National Archives, RG
                    59, Central Foreign Policy File, D770275–1146. Confidential; Immediate. Drafted
                    by Smith and Lewis; cleared in <gloss target="#t_PM_1">PM</gloss>, AFR/SFWA,
                        <gloss target="#t_NEA_1">NEA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_NEA_1"
                    >NEA</gloss>/EGY, and P; approved by <persName corresp="recKhGJMUCKyP9oj4"
                        >Moose</persName>. <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">Vance</persName>
                    was in Alexandria to meet with <persName corresp="recIigdM8sR9uq1Ip"
                        >Sadat</persName> to discuss the <placeName corresp="recJAi0OpNdSuYev5"
                        >Middle East</placeName> peace process.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1977-08-02T02:41:00+00:00">August 2, 1977, 0241Z</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Tosec 80036/180597. From <persName corresp="recKhGJMUCKyP9oj4">Moose</persName> to
                    <persName corresp="reclbVMhofbughnCg">Habib</persName>. Subject: Aid to
                    <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>. Ref: Secto 8006.<note
                    n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d22fn2">In telegram Secto 8006 from the Secretary’s
                    aircraft, August 1, <persName corresp="reclbVMhofbughnCg">Habib</persName>
                    wrote: “In anticipation of Egyptian interest could you let me have by immediate
                    return cable a summary of what we can realistically do for <placeName
                        corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> in military and <rs
                        type="topic" corresp="recSbJDXr0mWQQ76Q">economic aid</rs> in the immediate
                    future. The Secretary would like to move ahead on this without delay. Also, sum
                    up the results of our discussions with other countries and what they are doing
                    or are willing to do.” (National Archives, RG 59, Central Foreign Policy File,
                    D770274–0830)</note>
            </p>
            <p>1. Realistically, we can do very little for <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn"
                    >Chad</placeName> in either military or <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recSbJDXr0mWQQ76Q">economic aid</rs> in the near future.</p>
            <p>2. The principal constraints in <rs type="topic" corresp="recqk8lOkxJSwBcby">military
                    aid</rs> are the provisions in our own legislation and the fact that <placeName
                    corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> has no money. Grant assistance
                would require specific <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">congressional</orgName>
                authorization, and for practical purposes is out of the question. <placeName
                    corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> is not eligible for <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">Foreign Military Sales</rs> (<gloss
                    target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss>), but we are preparing a draft Presidential Determination that sales of <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="recOz4p561G66Gv2s">defense articles</rs> and services to
                    <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> under <gloss
                    target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> will strengthen the security of the <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> and promote world peace.<note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d22fn3">See <ref
                        target="#d24">Document 24</ref>.</note> Such a determination is a condition
                of <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> eligibility. Under present circumstances, the only way <placeName
                    corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> can obtain <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recJ9z9SORjaCLZG1">military equipment</rs> from the <gloss
                    target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> is to buy it from commercial sources. <placeName
                    corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>’s Foreign Minister is about to
                leave for Jidda, and presumably will request financing to purchase <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recJ9z9SORjaCLZG1">military equipment</rs>. If the President were to
                determine that <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> is eligible
                for <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss>, <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> could purchase
                through <gloss target="#t_DOD_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recjQ97iMHKp6vwlA">DOD</orgName>
                </gloss> but would still require financing. <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn"
                    >Chad</placeName> is not interested in credit, except on the most favorable
                terms. If <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> were <gloss
                    target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> eligible, and we were able to reprogram <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss>
                77 funds, it might be possible to arrange <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> credits for <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>. We are
                asking <gloss target="#t_PM_1">PM</gloss> to look into this possibility. I
                understand there is already quite a list of claimants, including <placeName
                    corresp="recsHWPUpdUAMACXO">Lebanon</placeName> and <placeName
                    corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>.</p>
            <p>3. <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> could obtain <gloss
                    target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> origin equipment through <rs type="topic" corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu"
                    >transfers</rs> from third countries. <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn"
                    >Chad</placeName> has approached <placeName corresp="recfpFrNXC2mjKxLP"
                    >Zaire</placeName>, <placeName corresp="recr6k8TVXxEPlyr5">Gabon</placeName>,
                    <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName>, <placeName
                    corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW">Egypt</placeName> and <placeName
                    corresp="recT1ZO3iDiD8XTeX">Sudan</placeName> and will raise third country <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu">transfers</rs> with <placeName
                    corresp="recXEA0LEpEd93tFt">Saudi Arabia</placeName> and perhaps <placeName
                    corresp="recXAkhh1lj7eIUzh">Jordan</placeName>. (FYI: <placeName
                    corresp="recr6k8TVXxEPlyr5">Gabon</placeName> has declined to provide further
                assistance to <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> because
                President <persName corresp="recyAF6NgK1HCQqsL">Bongo</persName> is now President of
                    <gloss target="#t_OAU_1">
                    <orgName corresp="reclJ1I8Ix3s26TFu">OAU</orgName>
                </gloss>. <placeName corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW">Egypt</placeName> has no <gloss
                    target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> origin lethal equipment and little if anything else from <pb facs="0062"
                    n="41" xml:id="pg_41"/>
                <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> which would help Chadians.) <rs type="topic" corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu"
                    >Transfers</rs> of <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> origin equipment/services to a country that is not <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> eligible, such as <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>,
                require a determination by the Secretary that the <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> would be willing to transfer the equipment in question directly to
                    <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>, and that the proposed
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu">transfers</rs> will strengthen the
                security of the <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> and promote world peace. Furthermore, before <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu">transfers</rs> of <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> origin items are approved, <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM"
                    >Congress</orgName> must be notified 30 working days in advance.</p>
            <p>4. Increasing our <rs type="topic" corresp="recSbJDXr0mWQQ76Q">economic aid</rs> to
                    <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> in the short-run will be
                extremely difficult. We have a <rs type="topic" corresp="recEmfen6T5wplQqD">
                    <gloss target="#t_PL480_1">PL–480</gloss> Title II</rs> program designed to make
                up shortfalls in last year’s harvest. This program is valued at 7 million dols,
                about half of which is the value of the commodities and about half the cost of
                transporting it to <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>. Chad has
                requested, as part of its <rs type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military
                    assistance</rs> package, 50 tons of rice but we cannot provide this under <gloss
                    target="#t_PL480_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="receYZXmZSuptfeyg">PL–480</rs>
                </gloss> because <gloss target="#t_PL480_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="receYZXmZSuptfeyg">PL–480</rs>
                </gloss> cannot be used for military purposes. The principal problem in the present
                    <gloss target="#t_PL480_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="receYZXmZSuptfeyg">PL–480</rs>
                </gloss> program has been a bottleneck at the railhead in <placeName
                    corresp="recCpTSVinGuQcpvv">Cameroon</placeName> (N’Gaoundere) which has now
                been broken. <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> had requested
                an <rs type="topic" corresp="recu0jAoErrAESV42">airlift</rs> to distribute food
                within <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>, which we turned down
                because it was not, and is not now, necessary. An <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recu0jAoErrAESV42">airlift</rs> at this point would be a dramatic
                demonstration of our support for <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn"
                    >Chad</placeName>, but would also be expensive and unnecessary, and would not
                directly assist <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> in
                maintaining its <rs type="topic" corresp="recAPhAIrM8XS4R2T">territorial
                    integrity</rs>.</p>
            <p>5. Our <rs type="topic" corresp="recVhimg8ze6j8WEs">economic assistance</rs> to
                    <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> in <gloss
                    target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 77 amounts to about 4 million dols, chiefly devoted
                to increasing food production over the long-run. It would be very difficult to
                accelerate any plans now in preparation to increase this assistance.</p>
            <p>6. In sum, subject to our readiness to take necessary policy decisions, for the time
                being the best advice we can give <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn"
                    >Chad</placeName> is to solicit financing from countries such as <placeName
                    corresp="recXEA0LEpEd93tFt">Saudi Arabia</placeName> in order to be able to buy
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recJ9z9SORjaCLZG1">military equipment</rs> from the
                    <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> or elsewhere through commercial channels. A somewhat more lengthy and
                complex procedure would be to solicit such <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu">transfers</rs> of <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> origin equipment from other countries as <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> would agree to.</p>
            <p>7. <persName corresp="recIigdM8sR9uq1Ip">Sadat</persName> may raise with you the
                possibility of replacing <rs type="topic" corresp="recJ9z9SORjaCLZG1">military
                    equipment</rs> including small arms, which are not of <gloss target="#t_US_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName>
                </gloss> origin, to <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>.
                Presidential Determination on arms for <placeName corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW"
                    >Egypt</placeName> has now been signed.<note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d22fn4"
                    >In telegram Secto 8025 from Alexandria, August 2, <persName
                        corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">Vance</persName> summarized his meeting on
                        <placeName corresp="rech4Y08vWrfyBSYC">Africa</placeName> and bilateral
                    issues with <persName corresp="recIigdM8sR9uq1Ip">Sadat</persName>. (National
                    Archives, RG 59, Central Foreign Policy File, P840072–2615)</note> We could
                consider providing <placeName corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW">Egypt</placeName> with
                replacements for such equipment. However, this would require consultations with the
                    <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> and could impact
                adversely on our “non-lethal” package on <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">the
                    Hill</orgName>.</p>
            <pb facs="0063" n="42" xml:id="pg_42"/>
            <p>8. In our discussions with other countries on assistance to <placeName
                    corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>, we have found very little support
                for a meeting of potential donors. The <placeName corresp="recJuFaVGGmK95QOO"
                    >French</placeName> have suggested a concertation of assistance through a series
                of bilateral contacts. <placeName corresp="recsMAoWbTPQ8P24I">Belgium</placeName>
                and the <gloss target="#t_FRG_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recUe17pTh04JBoo9">FRG</placeName>
                </gloss> may be possible sources of <rs type="topic" corresp="recm5bcRb25jCek8u"
                    >economic assistance</rs>, but are unlikely to provide <placeName
                    corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> with any <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military assistance</rs>. Also, it appears that
                    <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName> and the <placeName
                    corresp="recT1ZO3iDiD8XTeX">Sudan</placeName>, though sympathetic to <placeName
                    corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>, may only be able to provide at the
                most very little <rs type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military
                    assistance</rs> such as small arms and ammunition. Embassy Jidda believes
                    <placeName corresp="recXEA0LEpEd93tFt">Saudi Arabia</placeName> would be willing
                to participate financially in a multilateral effort. Embassy Tehran believes
                    <placeName corresp="recce2VRC74PP1qXq">Iran</placeName> would not finance
                Chadian arms purchases, but might contribute to common pool intended to assist
                    <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> economically. <placeName
                    corresp="recXEA0LEpEd93tFt">Saudi Arabia</placeName>, <placeName
                    corresp="recce2VRC74PP1qXq">Iran</placeName> and possibly <placeName
                    corresp="recXAkhh1lj7eIUzh">Jordan</placeName> could be sources of third country
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu">transfers</rs>. At the moment
                    <placeName corresp="recJuFaVGGmK95QOO">France</placeName> is providing
                    <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> with logistical
                equipment support and technical assistance. <placeName corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW"
                    >Egypt</placeName> is giving small arms, ammunition, and spare parts. <placeName
                    corresp="recr6k8TVXxEPlyr5">Gabon</placeName> has provided an aircraft but, as
                noted, <placeName corresp="recr6k8TVXxEPlyr5">Gabon</placeName> has declined to
                provide more assistance.</p>
            <p>9. As to possible Saudi financial assistance, Secretary may wish to raise topic
                during his meetings in Jidda.<note n="5" place="foot" xml:id="d22fn5">
                    <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">Vance</persName> was in Taif August 7–9 to
                    discuss the <placeName corresp="recJAi0OpNdSuYev5">Middle East</placeName> peace
                    process with Saudi leaders. There is no indication that he discussed Saudi
                    assistance to <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName>. See <ref
                        target="frus1969-76v08#d74">
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, vol. VIII,
                        Arab-Israeli Dispute, January 1977–August 1978, Documents 74</ref>, <ref
                        target="frus1969-76v08#d75">75</ref>, and <ref target="frus1969-76v08#d77"
                        >77</ref>.</note>
            </p>
            <p>10. In sum, as soon as <placeName corresp="recYyQtgN8smHlecn">Chad</placeName> can
                find a source of financing some non-lethal equipment (e.g., uniforms, rations) be
                made available from commercial sources in a matter of three to four weeks. Delivery
                would probably also require financing.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="rec9EBLnqQPcxRtYr">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Christopher</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
